doc.after: Some words can be different even significantly so in different Hispanophone countries Most Spanish speakers can recognize other Spanish forms even in places where they are not commonly used but Spaniards generally do not recognize specifically American usages For example Spanish mantequilla aguacate and albaricoque respectively butter avocado apricot correspond to manteca palta and damasco respectively in Argentina Chile except manteca Paraguay Peru except manteca and damasco and Uruguay
